Handling exceptions when closing a file
    try:
        file = open("learning", "r")
        content = file.read()
        print(content)
    finally:
        file.close()

>> try - starts the block to handle code that might raise an error
   open() - opens the file in read mode 
   read() - reads the content of the file 
   finally - ensures the code inside it runs no matter what 


OS Module 
.provides functions for interacting with the operating system 
.provides a portable way of using operating system-dependent functionality 


OS-Module Functions 
.Currently Working Directory - folder where Python is currently operating 
    .Python searches for files here when they are opened without specifying a full path 
    .this directory may be different from the location where the Python script is stored 

>getting the CWD  
    .to get the location of the CWD, the os.getcwd() function from the os module is used 
            import os 
            cwd = os.getcwd() 
            print("Current working directory:", cwd)

    .changing current working directory 
        .using os.chdir(path) - which switches Python's context to the specified directory 
        